@startuml seq-key-rotation
title Key and Credential Rotation Flow

participant "Consumer Sentinel" as csent
participant "Vault (Consumer)" as cvault
participant "Discovery API" as disc
participant "Discovery DB" as db
participant "SentinelRegistry\n(Blockchain)" as chain

note over csent
  Rotation is triggered by:
  (a) Scheduled key rotation policy (e.g., every 90 days)
  (b) Imminent VC expiry (detected by background timer)
  (c) Manual admin-initiated rotation
  (d) Suspected key compromise
end note

== Phase 1: Generate new key pair ==

csent -> csent: generate_did_key()\n→ new_private_key, new_did

csent -> cvault: kv/write\nsecret/sentinel/prod/consumer-app/private_key_pending\n{ private_key_bytes: new_key }
cvault --> csent: ok

== Phase 2: Update DID registration ==

csent -> disc: PATCH /api/v1/sentinels/did:key:z6Mk<OLD>\n{\n  "new_did": "did:key:z6Mk<NEW>",\n  "new_public_key_jwk": {...},\n  "rotation_proof": "<JWS signed by OLD key over {old_did, new_did, ts}>"\n}\nAuthorization: Bearer <session-token>

disc -> disc: Verify rotation_proof with OLD public key\n(proves possession of old key)

disc -> chain: sentinelRegistry.rotate\n(old_did, new_did, new_pubkey_hash)
chain --> disc: txHash

disc -> db: UPDATE sentinels\n  SET did=new_did, public_key=new_jwk,\n  old_did=old_did, rotation_tx=txHash

disc -> db: INSERT audit_log\n{ action=SENTINEL_ROTATED, old_did, new_did, ts }

disc --> csent: 200 OK\n{\n  "new_did": "did:key:z6Mk<NEW>",\n  "old_did_status": "GRACE_PERIOD",\n  "grace_period_ends": "ISO8601 + 5min"\n}

== Phase 3: Sentinel switches to new key ==

csent -> cvault: kv/write\nsecret/sentinel/prod/consumer-app/private_key\n{ private_key_bytes: new_key }
cvault --> csent: ok

csent -> cvault: kv/delete\nsecret/sentinel/prod/consumer-app/private_key_pending
cvault --> csent: ok

== Phase 4: Re-issue VC with new DID ==

csent -> disc: POST /api/v1/credentials\n{\n  "consumer_did": "did:key:z6Mk<NEW>",\n  "producer_service_id": "citizen-data",\n  "env": "prod",\n  "scope": [...]\n}\nAuthorization: Bearer <new-session-token-signed-by-new-key>

disc -> disc: Issue new VC (see seq-vc-issuance)
disc --> csent: 201 Created { "credential": "<new-jwt-vc>" }

csent -> csent: Replace stored VC\nBegin using new key + new VC

note over disc
  Grace period: during GRACE_PERIOD_SECONDS (default: 300s)
  the old DID is still accepted by Producer Sentinels
  that haven't refreshed their DID resolution cache yet.
  After grace period, old DID is DEPRECATED on-chain.
end note

@enduml
